description: Garden State Canoeing contains descriptions of 105 canoeable New Jersey waterways with over 250 possible trips described. Detailed maps showing put-in and take-out spots along with specific river descriptions are included. The descriptions also contain mileage, USGS gauges, weirs, dams, nearby roads and other points of interest. Water levels using USGS gauge references are given for determining if a rivers water level is suitable for canoeing.
